The course provides an overview of a variety of psychological intervention methods, and gives opportunities  to practice designing psychological interventions, delivering psychological intervention measures and plan evaluation of psychological interventions in sport and performance settings.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to study main methods in sport and performance psychology interventions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will be able to 1. explain principles of intervention planning in sport and performance settings 2. design psychological performance enhancement interventions 3. design interventions for removing psychological barriers to performance excellence  4. design interventions for career transitions in sport and performance settings 5. design crisis interventions in sport and performance settings 6. design psychological rehabilitation of injuries in sport and performance settings 7. design evaluation of psychological interventions in sport and performance settings
